OL,3,CNo 10 won't re-think winter fuel
OL,4,Cdespite admitting it hurt them at
OL,5,Cballot box
OL,7,FThe government has doubled down on its
OL,8,Funpopular decision to cut winter fuel
OL,9,Fpayments, despite admitting it hurt
OL,10,Fthe Labour Party in the local
OL,11,Felections.
OL,13,FPrime Minister Sir Keir Starmer has
OL,14,Fcome under growing pressure to re-
OL,15,Fthink the controversial policy, as
OL,16,Fministers acknowledged the public's
OL,17,Fanger over the decision to means-test
OL,18,Fthe previously universal benefit
OL,19,Fcontributed to Labour's hammering at
OL,20,Fthe ballot box.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/15
