OL,4,Cdespite admitting it hurt them at
OL,5,Cballot box
OL,7,FThe prime minister's official
OL,8,Fspokesman also confirmed "there will
OL,9,Fnot be a change to the government's
OL,10,Fpolicy" and that the decision "was one
OL,11,Fthat we had to take to ensure economic
OL,12,Fstability and repair the public
OL,13,Ffinances following the #22 billion
OL,14,Fblack hole left by the previous
OL,15,Fgovernment".
OL,17,FHe added that the government will not
OL,18,Fbe "blown off course" after the local
OL,19,Felection results, insisting: "We were
OL,20,Felected as a stable and serious party
OL,21,Fafter 14 years of chaos and decline."
